
[1]ton

   TON, the termination of names of places,is town.

   TON, n. The prevailing fashion.

   TON, n. The weight of twenty hundred gross. [See Tun.] This is false
   orthography. The word is from the Saxon tunna, a cask, and the sense of
   weight is taken from that of a cask or butt.
